    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1964-10-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1964-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="306"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                <head>306. Memorandum From Secretary of Defense McNamara to the Chairman of the
                    Joint Chiefs of Staff (<persName corresp="#p_WEG_1">Wheeler</persName>)<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d306fn1">Source: Washington National Records
                        Center, <gloss target="#t_RG_1">RG</gloss> 218, <gloss target="#t_JCS_1"
                            >JCS</gloss> Files, 9111 (64). Top Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1964-10-30">October 30, 1964</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You are authorized to order a reconnaissance flight over the Stanleyville area,
                    provided that the flight:</p>
                <pb facs="0477" n="444" xml:id="pg_444"/>
                <p>1. Will not be carried out before Monday, November 2nd.</p>
                <p>2. Will be made by a C–97 aircraft.</p>
                <p>3. Proceed according to a flight plan filed in advance.</p>
                <p>4. Fly in an altitude of 10,000 feet or above and no closer than 10 miles to
                    Stanleyville.</p>
                <p>Please develop the detailed operational plan for the mission and clear it with
                    State through ISA, and then through the Country Team, before issuing the
                    operational order to the appropriate commander.</p>
                <p>If you have any further questions on this matter, please consult with either Mr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName> or me.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d306fn2">During the October 30 meeting of the 303 Committee,
                            <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName> emphasized that the
                        Department of Defense was insistent about the necessity of a reconnaissance
                        flight over Stanleyville prior to the activation of any <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCSTRIKE_1">CINCSTRIKE</gloss> operation in that theatre,
                        and that a lead time of 7 days between accomplishment of the reconnaissance
                        mission and activation of such an operation would be required. (Central
                        Intelligence Agency Files, DCI/<persName corresp="#p_MJA_1"
                            >McCone</persName> Files, Job 80B01285A, 303 Committee Meetings
                        (1964))</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>McNamara<note n="3" xml:id="d306fn3">Printed from a copy that indicates
                            McNamara signed the original.</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
